AHEAD of the forthcoming Ramadan, the Association of Ikire Muslim Professionals (AIMP) will be holding its second public lecture entitled ‘Overcoming Trials’ tomorrow on the open field of Nawair-Ud Deen Grammar School, Sango, Ikire, Osun State, at 10.00 a.m. In a statement, the chairman of the planning committee, Mr Saheed Ademakinwa, said the pre-Ramadan lecture would be delivered by a prominent Lagos-based scholar, Dr AbdulHakeem AbdulLateef. AbdulLateef, who is the Imam of the Lagos State House of Assembly mosque, according to the statement, will be speaking on types of trials and how to overcome them. The chairman of the occasion is Alhaji Abdul Yekeen Toye Bamiduro, the statement added. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Ikire Muslim professionals  Ikire Muslim professionals Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Ikire Muslim professionals  Ikire Muslim professionals ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
